Package: ggcorpframe
Title: Corporate Design Frame for ggplot2 and PNG Images
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Simon", "Niederberger", email = "s.niederberger@hotmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Wraps ggplot2 plots or raw PNG images with a corporate design
    frame (header with title/subtitle, footer with footnotes/sources) via a
    Python/matplotlib subprocess. No Shiny dependency — works standalone for
    scripts, RMarkdown, and Quarto. Use shinycorpframe for Shiny integration.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/saemeon/dash-interact
Imports:
    ggplot2
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.0
Config/testthat/edition: 3
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.10), matplotlib
